From fbed7c49ffe59cd66e7587c8692dd41c4c498dcd Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: =?UTF-8?q?=C3=98yvind=20Harboe?= <oyvind.harboe@zylin.com>
Date: Fri, 15 May 2026 14:52:56 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] flow.bzl: pull synth into generate_metadata data deps
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

`orfs_generate_metadata`'s action only sees files that reach it via
the floorplan→cts forwarding chain (`forwarded_names = [CANON_OUTPUT]`)
plus whatever's passed in `data =`.  The chain forwards
`1_1_yosys_canonicalize.rtlil` but not the post-ABC netlist, so
`genMetrics.py` reads `1_2_yosys.v` from a path that does not exist
in the sandbox and `synth__netlist__hash` lands in `metadata.json`
as `N/A`.

The metadata test rule then surfaces:

    [WARN] synth__netlist__hash differs test: N/A == <make-sha>

— a useful tell only by accident, since any non-match yields N/A.

Add the synth step as a data dependency to the metadata step;
synth's DefaultInfo already exposes every result file (canon RTLIL,
`1_2_yosys.v`, `1_2_yosys.sdc`, `1_synth.sdc`, …) so this one line
is enough.  Touching every downstream stage's `forwarded_names` to
thread the netlist through floorplan→final would work too but is
considerably more invasive.

Verified on `//flow/designs/asap7/uart:uart_test`: bazel-side hash
moves from `N/A` to `ab8b0b69a2897be911f6f1bd7d0de1649160bc2a`
(make-side baseline `95652d905a7cf9bc9c935a58e01a76e65327c8b3`).

Signed-off-by: Øyvind Harboe <oyvind.harboe@zylin.com>
---
 private/flow.bzl | 8 ++++++++
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+)

diff --git a/private/flow.bzl b/private/flow.bzl
index b59d059..1519eb8 100644
--- a/private/flow.bzl
+++ b/private/flow.bzl
@@ -769,6 +769,14 @@ def _orfs_pass(
             data = [
                 # Need 2_floorplan.sdc
                 _step_name(name, variant, "floorplan"),
+                # Need 1_2_yosys.v for `synth__netlist__hash` and any
+                # other genMetrics.py field that reads synth results
+                # past the canonicalize RTLIL.  Only canonicalize is
+                # threaded through `forwarded_names = [CANON_OUTPUT]`
+                # along the floorplan→cts chain; the post-ABC netlist
+                # is not.  Pulling synth's outputs in via `data =`
+                # gives metadata access without touching every stage.
+                _step_name(name, variant, "synth"),
             ],
             kwargs = kwargs,
         )
-- 
